Try it with `flexbox`:

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-css --&gt;

    .main-footer {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: center;
        width: 100%;
        background-color: lightblue;
        padding: 2em;
        margin-top: 30px;
    }

    .main-footer li {
        float: left;
        font-size: 0.85em;
        padding: 0 0.5em;
        margin-bottom: 0.5em;
    }

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;footer class=&quot;main-footer&quot;&gt;
        &lt;ul&gt;
            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#&quot;&gt;Contact us&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
            &lt;li&gt;&amp;copy; Copyright Acme Industries 2019&lt;/li&gt;
        &lt;/ul&gt;
    &lt;/footer&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

First of all. NEVER use `float` for layout purposes. It messes up your content and it starts a snowball effect in your CSS.

`flex` is the way to go -&gt; [flexbox MDN][1] ( and other links )

Use `align-items: center` to align your items **vertically** and `justify-content: center` to align them **horizontally**.

Also, use `box-sizing: border-box` so the padding of the footer will be &#39;included&#39; in it&#39;s `100%` width and you don&#39;t have a scroll overflow on x-axis.



&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-css --&gt;

    .main-footer li {
      font-size: 0.85em;
      padding: 0 0.5em;
      margin-bottom: 0.5em;
      display: inline-block;
    }

    .main-footer {
      display: flex;
      align-items:center;
      justify-content: center;
      text-align: center;
      width: 100%;
      background-color: lightblue;
      padding: 2em;
      margin-top: 30px;
      box-sizing:border-box;
    }

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;footer class=&quot;main-footer&quot;&gt;
      &lt;ul&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#&quot;&gt;Contact us&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;&amp;copy; Copyright Acme Industries 2019&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;/ul&gt;
    &lt;/footer&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;


  [1]: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Flexible_Box_Layout/Basic_Concepts_of_Flexbox

In case you don&#39;t want to go the flex way, just change the display property of your UL element.

Something like this:



&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-css --&gt;

    .main-footer ul {
      display: inline-block;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
    }

    .main-footer li {
      float: left;
      font-size: 0.85em;
      padding: 0 0.5em;
      list-style-type: none;
    }

    .main-footer {
      text-align: center;
      width: 100%;
      background-color: lightblue;
      padding: 2em 0;
      margin-top: 30px;
    }

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;footer class=&quot;main-footer&quot;&gt;
      &lt;ul&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#&quot;&gt;Contact us&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;&amp;copy; Copyright Acme Industries 2019&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;/ul&gt;
    &lt;/footer&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

Set the `ul` as the flex container and remove the left and right padding from the `footer` container to ensure it&#39;s centered. The padding can be added to the `ul` instead.

Without flexbox, set the `li` elements to `display: inline-block`.

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: null --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-css --&gt;

    .main-footer {
      width: 100%;
      background-color: lightblue;
      padding: 2em 0;
      margin-top: 30px;
    }

    .main-footer ul {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: center;
      list-style: none;
    }

    .main-footer li {
      font-size: 0.85em;
      margin-right: 0.5em;
    }

    .main-footer li:last-child {
       margin-right: 0;
    }

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;footer class=&quot;main-footer&quot;&gt;
      &lt;ul&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#&quot;&gt;Contact us&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;&amp;copy; Copyright Acme Industries 2019&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;/ul&gt;
    &lt;/footer&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

With float, you are forcing elements to be pulled towards the left. 
Use display:inline-block to make the element in center, as parent is already text-align:center



&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: null --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-css --&gt;

    .main-footer li {
