You need to address the [`/drives`][1] collection rather than the default `/drive`. You can retrieve the list of Drives that belong to a site by calling:

```
GET /v1.0/sites/{siteId}/drives?select=id,name
```

This will return a collection of `drive` resources:

``` json
{
    &quot;@odata.context&quot;: &quot;https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0/$metadata#drives&quot;,
    &quot;value&quot;: [
        {
            &quot;id&quot;: &quot;id1&quot;,
            &quot;name&quot;: &quot;Documents&quot;
        },
        {
            &quot;id&quot;: &quot;id2&quot;,
            &quot;name&quot;: &quot;Other Documents&quot;
        }

    ]
}
```

You can then address the [`drive`][2] by `id` like this:

```
GET /v1.0/sites/{siteId}/drives/{driveId}
```


  [1]: https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/graph/api/resources/site?view=graph-rest-1.0#relationships
  [2]: https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/graph/api/resources/drive?view=graph-rest-1.0
